SIMPLE: interpenetrate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interpenetrate
<hw>In`ter*pen"e*trate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To
penetrate between or within; to penetrate mutually.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It <qex>interpenetrates</qex> my granite mass.</q>
<rj><qau>Shelley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interpenetrate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Interpenetrate
<hw>In`ter*pen"e*trate</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To penetrate each the
other; to penetrate between bodies or their parts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Interpenetrating molding</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>,
<cd>in late Gothic architecture, a decoration by means of moldings which
seem to pass through solid uprights, transoms, or other members; often,
two sets of architectural members penetrating one another, in
appearance, as if both had been plastic when they were put
together.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interpenetration</ent>⟦br⟧
